@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
title 09 – Polimorfizm: jedna operacja, wiele implementacji

abstract class Shape {
  + {abstract} area() : float
  + {abstract} perimeter() : float
  + describe() : str
  + scale(factor: float) : Shape
}

class Rectangle {
  - _w: float
  - _h: float
  --
  + __init__(w: float, h: float)
  + area() : float
  + perimeter() : float
  + __str__() : str
}

class Circle {
  - _r: float
  --
  + __init__(r: float)
  + area() : float
  + perimeter() : float
  + __str__() : str
}

class Triangle {
  - _base: float
  - _height: float
  - _sides: tuple[float,float,float]
  --
  + __init__(base, height, a, b, c)
  + area() : float
  + perimeter() : float
  + __str__() : str
}

class RegularPolygon {
  - _n: int
  - _side: float
  --
  + __init__(n: int, side: float)
  + area() : float
  + perimeter() : float
}

Shape <|-- Rectangle
Shape <|-- Circle
Shape <|-- Triangle
Shape <|-- RegularPolygon

note top of Shape
  **Polimorfizm** – ta sama sygnatura,
  różne implementacje.
  Funkcja ""total_area(shapes)"" działa
  dla **dowolnej** podklasy Shape,
  bez instrukcji if/isinstance.
end note

note bottom of Rectangle
  ""shapes = [Rectangle(3,4), Circle(2), Triangle(6,4,6,5,5)]""
